# Package Structure

Root package: `com.chriswininger`

## Domain packages under `api/`

Each domain feature lives in its own package under `com.chriswininger.api` with a consistent internal layout:

```
com.chriswininger.api.<domain>/
  ├── <Domain>Resource.java        # JAX-RS endpoint(s)
  ├── dto/                         # Domain-specific DTOs (records)
  │   └── requests/                # Request/response DTOs
  └── services/                    # Business logic services
```

Current domains: `documents`, `semanticsearch`.

When adding a new feature area, create a new domain package following this pattern rather than adding to an existing one.

## Cross-cutting API packages

- `com.chriswininger.api` — shared API constants (`ApiConstants`)
- `com.chriswininger.api.services.inferenceapi` — LLM inference services (`OllamaApiService`)
- `com.chriswininger.api.dto.inferenceresults` — inference result records and `@InferenceDescription`

## Infrastructure packages

| Package | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `com.chriswininger.ai` | CDI producers for LangChain4j models, embedding stores, and AI service interfaces |
| `com.chriswininger.db` | `DSLContextProducer` and DB wiring |
| `com.chriswininger.repository` | One `@ApplicationScoped` repository per table, using jOOQ `DSLContext` |

## Placement guide

| You're adding… | Put it in… |
|----------------|-----------|
| New REST endpoint for an existing domain | `api.<domain>/<Name>Resource.java` |
| New feature area | `api.<newdomain>/` with resource, `dto/`, `services/` |
| New DTO for a domain | `api.<domain>.dto.requests/` (or `dto/` if not a request/response) |
| New business service | `api.<domain>.services/` |
| New repository | `repository/` |
| New CDI producer for AI/ML | `ai/` |
| New DB infrastructure | `db/` |
